  "body": "**üßê Motivation**\r\nSupport the EIP2535 Standard for upgradeable contracts.  \r\n\r\n**üìù Details**\r\nThis is a transpiler upgrade to generate Upgradeable EIP2535 Diamond Storage enabled contracts.  This repo is generated just as the openzeppelin-contracts-upgradable one is with transpiler converting to EIP2535 standard that uses storage slots instead of gaps for storage.  This is still a WIP, but I plan on having it finished in the next couple of days.\r\n\r\nI would like to have a fork repo created under the OpenZeppelin Organization to push the new repo back into.  But if not feasible, I can keep the current repo URL: https://github.com/GeniusVentures/openzeppelin-contracts-diamond.\r\n\r\nA pull request has already been submitted to the transpiler repo as well, but it is probably better pulled when completed.\r\n\r\n\r\n",
